title: ZENITH Definition & Meaning - Merriam-Webster
snippet: When you reach the zenith, you're at the top, the pinnacle, the summit, the peak. Zenith developed from an Arabic phrase meaning "the way over one's head," and then traveled through Old Spanish, Medieval Latin, and Middle French before arriving in English.

title: Zenith - LVMH
snippet: Founded in 1865 in Le Locle, Switzerland, ZENITH has been synonymous with the avant-garde of watchmaking for over 160 years, driven by a pioneering spirit and an unwavering quest for precision.
